'''日本鬼-{zh-cn:{{ruby-py|子|zǐ}};zh-tw:{{ruby-zy|子|ㄗˇ}}}-'''（{{jpn|rm=Hinomoto Oniko|hg=ひのもと　おにこ|j=日本 鬼子}}）是一个2010年于日本[[2ch|2ch]]论坛news4vip板块创造的[[萌|萌]]系角色，并且在日本的多个论坛[[網路爆紅|爆红]]。该角色为中文里对日本人的贬称“日本鬼子”的[[萌拟人化|萌拟人化]]演绎形象。并以此来进行对日本鬼子的美化，以及消除大众对日本鬼子野蛮、无恶不作的形象<ref name=libertytimes>{{Cite web |url=https://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/paper/439975 |title=萌系日本鬼子 反攻中國 - 國際 - 自由時報電子報 |access-date=2020-01-05 |archive-date=2018-03-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180318070118/http://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/paper/439975 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=searchina>{{cite news|url=http://news.searchina.ne.jp/disp.cgi?y=2010&d=1104&f=national_1104_129.shtml|title=百度で「日本鬼子」を検索すると、検索候補に「萌化」が出現|publisher=Searchina News|language=ja|date=4 November 2010|accessdate=21 January 2011|archive-date=2014-09-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140902105138/http://news.searchina.ne.jp/disp.cgi?y=2010&d=1104&f=national_1104_129.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=dailyonigiri>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailyonigiri.com/2010/10/japan-strikes-back-at-anti-japanese-protests-in-china-with-a-moe-character/|title=Japan strikes back at anti-Japanese protests in China with a moe character|publisher=DailyOnigiri|date=October 31, 2010|accessdate=January 27, 2011|archive-date=2017-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170629055630/http://www.dailyonigiri.com/2010/10/japan-strikes-back-at-anti-japanese-protests-in-china-with-a-moe-character/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==背景==
这个角色最初是由2ch板块的用户为[[讽刺|讽刺]]上述中文词汇构想的。<ref name=libertytimes/><ref name=singtao>{{cite news|url=http://news.singtao.ca/toronto/2010-12-06/world1291629598d2884859.html|title=「日本鬼子」漫畫對抗中國責罵聲|language=zh|publisher=Singtao Daily|date=6 December 2010|accessdate=21 January 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140226073129/http://news.singtao.ca/toronto/2010-12-06/world1291629598d2884859.html|archive-date=2014-02-26|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name=nownews>{{cite news|url=http://www.nownews.com/2010/11/24/334-2667213.htm|title=萬物皆可萌　日網友將「小日本」變身美少女|language=zh|publisher=NOWnews|date=24 November 2010|accessdate=21 January 2011|archive-date=2012-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120928151915/http://www.nownews.com/2010/11/24/334-2667213.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>在[[中国|中国]]，[[日本鬼子|日本鬼子]]是一个从[[二战|二战]]时期开始广泛使用的词语，并且沿用至今，成为对日本人的贬称。日本民众选择了把一般的攻击和冒犯性质的词语转变成“可爱”或者“萌”的形象这一做法，以表现侮辱之后的负面内涵可被转换。<ref name=searchina/>这一形象的创作起于2010年由于长期的[[釣魚臺列嶼主權問題|钓鱼岛争端]]而引起的[[中国渔船与日本巡逻船钓鱼岛相撞事件|中国渔船与日本巡逻船钓鱼岛相撞事件]]以及由此在中国网民中引起的[[反日|反日]]情绪和中国人的岛屿主权争端的公众反应。<ref name=libertytimes/><ref name=searchina/>

==语源==
日语中“日本鬼子”通常[[音读|音读]]为“{{lang|ja|にほんきし}}”（Nihon kishi），但也可以[[训读|训读]]成女性人名“{{lang|ja|ひのもと　おにこ}}”（Hinomoto Oniko）。<ref name=dailyonigiri/>其中的[[日本人名|姓氏]]{{lang|ja|ひのもと}}字面意思为“[[日本的称号|日出之地]]”，并有日本女性人名常见的语尾“子”（{{lang|ja|こ}}）<ref name="Hakes122">{{cite book|last=Hakes|first=Molly|title=The Everything Conversational Japanese Book: Basic Instruction For Speaking This Fascinating Language In Any Setting|publisher=Everything Books|date=2004|url=//books.google.com/books?id=m2WaRtYHoUoC&pg=PA122&dq=%22Men's+names+are+often+long%22&hl=en&ei=WqNATsGPDcnJsQLazbCnCQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CC0Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=%22Men's%20names%20are%20often%20long%22&f=false|page=122|isbn=978-1-59337-147-0|access-date=2021-12-23|archive-date=2013-06-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130620222519/http://books.google.com/books?id=m2WaRtYHoUoC&pg=PA122&dq=%22Men%27s+names+are+often+long%22&hl=en&ei=WqNATsGPDcnJsQLazbCnCQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CC0Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=%22Men's%20names%20are%20often%20long%22&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>（如山田花子）。<ref>{{cite web|title=山田太郎から進化を続ける「名前例」|url=http://www.excite.co.jp/News/bit/E1328764726320.html|work=Excite Bit|publisher=Excite News|accessdate=6 December 2012|language=ja|date=20 February 2012|trans_title='Example Names' Continue to Evolve beyond Yamada Tarō|archive-date=2017-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171104115140/http://www.excite.co.jp/News/bit/E1328764726320.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==设-{}-定==
其形象为黑色长发，肤色白皙，身穿[[和服|和服]]的年轻女鬼（{{lang|ja|おに}}），头戴般若之面，手持日本刀或者薙刀。<!--The main design motif is based on the [[Oni_(folklore)|Oni]] in Japanese folklore. Since the character was designed to be a "personification" of the slur, she is portrayed as a young woman with long black hair and pale skin, often wearing a [[kimono|kimono]] and demon horns, whilst holding various motifs unique to Japanese culture, such as a [[naginata|naginata]] and a [[hannya|hannya]] mask.--><ref name=libertytimes/>该角色还有个变种即“{{lang|ja|こひのもと}}”（Ko-hinomoto），是由中文的另一贬称[[小日本|小日本]]萌化而来，被设-{}-定为可爱小女生，是日本鬼子的妹妹。

